South African media personality Bonang Matheba launched a new limited edition MCC. JOHANNESBURG - South African media personality and entrepreneur Bonang Matheba once again made headlines this weekend after she revealed her brand-new limited MCC at the Sun Met. The House of BNG was the official celebration partner of the event which was held in Cape Town. READ: Bonang Matheba to host Miss SA "...stopped by the 2020 @officialsunmet to introduce our new Prestige Reserve! Thank you @suninternationalza! Fun!', said Bonang in a post on Instagram. Matheba made history last year after she became the first black woman to become a member of the Cap Classique Producers Association following the launch of her own sparkling wine range. ....stopped by the 2020 @officialsunmet to introduce our new Prestige Reserve! Thank you @suninternationalza! Fun! 🎉💕💐 #SunMet2020 #HouseOfBNG A post shared by  Bonang Matheba (@bonang_m) on Feb 1, 2020 at 10:57am PST Say hello to my new baby... BNG Prestige Reserve. 👑 @houseofbng A post shared by  Bonang Matheba (@bonang_m) on Feb 1, 2020 at 11:58am PST BNG. 👑 #HouseOfBNG A post shared by  Bonang Matheba (@bonang_m) on Feb 1, 2020 at 11:59pm PST